==English==

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|despair||}}
# To be hopeless; to have no hope; to give up all hope or expectation; - often with ''of''.

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|despair||}}
# To give up as beyond hope or expectation; to despair of (obsolete).
# To cause to despair (obsolete).  

===Noun===
'''despair'''
# Loss of hope; utter hopelessness; complete despondency.
#:''He turned around '''in despair''', knowing he won't survive''
# That which is despaired of.

===Synonyms===
# Desperation
# Despondency
# Hopelessness.

